icture that’s displayed on your desktop. Your Mac comes with dozens of desktop pictures to choose from, or you can use your own pictures or choose a solid color.</p><figure><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/ccf7f81db24a8e726336ecfef8033abe.png\" alt=\"The Desktop pane of System Preferences.\" height=\"391\" width=\"466\" originalImageName=\"Art/S0004_DesktopPrefs.png\"></figure><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Tip\"><strong class=\"tip\">Tip: </strong>You can drag an image from your desktop or a folder onto the thumbnail at the top of the pane to use the image as your desktop picture.</p></div><div id=\"mchlpc3db0c6\" class=\"Task no-header\"><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchlpc3db0c6\"><ol><li><p>On your Mac, choose Apple menu <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/e043ddf1a45711e13f0b30612db65e21.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo.png\"> &gt; System Preferences, click Desktop &amp; Screen Saver, then click Desktop.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.preference.desktopscreeneffect&amp;anchorId=DesktopPref\" class=\"URL\">Open the Desktop pane for me</a></p></li><li><p>On the left, find a picture or color:</p><ul><li><p><em>Pictures and colors that come with your Mac: </em>Click the disclosure triangle next to Apple, then select Desktop Pictures or Colors to see thumbnails of available pictures and colors.</p><p>Dynamic Desktop pictures automatically change throughout the course of the day based on your current location. If Location Services is <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-privacy-preferences-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH32356&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">turned off in Privacy preferences</a>, the picture changes based on the time zone specified in Date &amp; Time preferences.</p><p>Some dynamic desktop pictures may provide still images so the desktop picture doesn’t distract from the light or dark appearance. For example, if you chose the dark appearance during macOS setup, the desktop picture is set to a dark still image. To use or stop using a still image (if available), click the dynamic desktop thumbnail, then choose an option from the pop-up menu that appears.</p></li><li><p><em>Your pictures: </em>Click the disclosure triangle next to Photos (or iPhoto if available). If your pictures are in the Pictures or another folder, click the triangle next to Folders, then select a folder.</p><p>To add a folder, click the Add button <span class=\"NoBreak\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/915da4d2f890e0cf0f74d4410c68b13a.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"32\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AddListItem_osx.png\">, </span>navigate to and <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=select-items&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLB6D352A4&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">select the folder</a>, then click Choose.</p><p>If you don’t see anything when you select the folder that contains your pictures, they might not have the right file format—JPEG, PICT, TIFF, PNG, or HEIC. To change a picture’s format, open it in the Preview app, then save it in the new format. If pictures look fuzzy, try using larger ones, such as 1024 x 768 pixels.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>On the right, click the picture you want to use. </p><p>The desktop immediately changes, so you can see how the picture looks. When you use one of your own pictures, you can choose to have it fill the screen, be centered, or otherwise arranged. It’s easy to click around and try different pictures and arrangements until you find the one you like best.</p><p>To use all the pictures in a folder, select the “Change picture” checkbox, then choose how often you want the picture to change—for example, every hour. The pictures are shown in the order they appear in the folder, or you can choose to show them in a random order.</p></li></ol></div></div><p>To quickly use a picture you have in the Photos app, select the picture in Photos, click the Share button <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/6bc766c1653e5e0ce440d2fbc1005533.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"26\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_shareButton_osx.png\"> in the Photos toolbar, then choose Set Desktop Picture.</p><p>You can use a picture you see on the web as your desktop picture. Control-click the image in the browser window, then select Use Image as Desktop Picture.</p><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=desktop&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH40612&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Get to know the Mac desktop</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=dock&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH35859&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Use the Dock on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=manage-windows&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP2469&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Manage windows on Mac</a><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=make-it-easier-to-see-whats-on-the-screen&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLD786F2CD&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Make it easier to see what’s on the screen of your Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"3950"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Unarchived","name":"Unarchived","englishName":"Unarchived","displayName":"Unarchived","articleCount":"10186"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndexON","name":"ExternalIndexON","englishName":"ExternalIndexON","displayName":"ExternalIndexON","articleCount":"4683"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"7818"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac","articleCount":"7510"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"platform","displayName":"platform","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"macOS Mojave 10.14","name":"macOS Mojave 10.14","englishName":"macOS Mojave 10.14","displayName":"